        <div n="662-36L-" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"><hi rend="underline">Written in the Year </hi>1733.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">P</hi>OOR Ladies! though their Bus'ness be to play,</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-2"> 'Tis hard they must be busy Night and Day:</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-3"> Why should they want the Privilege of Men,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-4"> And take some small Diversions now and then?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-5"> Had Women been the Makers of our Laws;</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-6"> (And why they were not, I can see no Cause;)</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-7"> The Men should slave at Cards from Morn to Night;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-662-36L--line-8"> And Female Pleasures be to read and write.</l></lg></div>
      </div>
